g='All-Wheel Drive Dual Motor', text='All-Wheel Drive Dual Motor', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/12', parent=RefItem(cref='#/pictures/4'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.CAPTION: 'caption'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=3, bbox=BoundingBox(l=144.1241, t=98.57529999999997, r=255.07930000000005, b=91.38624656488548, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 27))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Performance All-Wheel Drive', text='Performance All-Wheel Drive', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), SectionHeaderItem(self_ref='#/texts/13', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.SECTION_HEADER: 'section_header'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=3, bbox=BoundingBox(l=460.8, t=524.9759, r=642.7271999999999, b=476.3342286004057, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 26))], source=[], comments=[], orig='All-Wheel Drive Dual Motor', text='All-Wheel Drive Dual Motor', formatting=None, hyperlink=None, level=1), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/14', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=3, bbox=BoundingBox(l=460.8, t=450.1843, r=686.0120000000004, b=366.2116091603054, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 288))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Dual Motor Model S is a categorical improvement on conventional all-wheel drive systems. With two motors, one in the front and one in the rear, Model S digitally and independently controls torque to the front and rear wheels. The result is unparalleled traction control in all conditions.', text='Dual Motor Model S is a categorical improvement on conventional all-wheel drive systems. With two motors, one in the front and one in the rear, Model S digitally and independently controls torque to the front and rear wheels. The result is unparalleled traction control in all conditions.', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/15', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=3, bbox=BoundingBox(l=460.8, t=345.1843, r=670.8810000000002, b=231.21160916030533, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 355))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Conventional all-wheel drive cars employ complex mechanical linkages to distribute power from a single engine to all four wheels. This sacrifices efficiency in favor of all weather traction. In contrast, each Model S motor is lighter, smaller and more efficient than its rear wheel drive counterpart, providing both improved range and faster acceleration.', text='Conventional all-wheel drive cars employ complex mechanical linkages to distribute power from a single engine to all four wheels. This sacrifices efficiency in favor of all weather traction. In contrast, each Model S motor is lighter, smaller and more efficient than its rear wheel drive counterpart, providing both improved range and faster acceleration.', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/16', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=3, bbox=BoundingBox(l=460.8, t=210.1843, r=677.351, b=111.21160916030533, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 308))], source=[], comments=[], orig='All-wheel drive is standard on Model S 70D and available as an option on Model S 85. Model S Performance comes standard with All-Wheel Drive Dual Motor, pairing the high performance rear motor with a high efficiency front motor to achieve supercar acceleration, from zero to 60 miles per hour in 3.1 seconds.', text='All-wheel drive is standard on Model S 70D and available as an option on Model S 85. Model S Performance comes standard with All-Wheel Drive Dual Motor, pairing the high performance rear motor with a high efficiency front motor to achieve supercar acceleration, from zero to 60 miles per hour in 3.1 seconds.', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), SectionHeaderItem(self_ref='#/texts/17', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.SECTION_HEADER: 'section_header'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=4, bbox=BoundingBox(l=202.8879, t=419.1103, r=589.1126999999999, b=398.47662860040566, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 32))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Highest Safety Rating in America', text='Highest Safety Rating in America', formatting=None, hyperlink=None, level=1), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/18', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=4, bbox=BoundingBox(l=265.1908, t=384.0701, r=526.8091999999998, b=377.09545211267607, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 50))], source=[], comments=[], orig='THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION', text='THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/19', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=4, bbox=BoundingBox(l=201.60180000000003, t=349.23359999999997, r=593.0008000000003, b=250.26090916030535, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 516))], source=[], comments=[], orig=\"Model S is designed from the ground up to be the safest car on the road, as proven by a 5-star rating in all categories of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) crash test. Much of its safety is owed to the unique electric drivetrain that sits beneath the car's aluminum occupant cell in its own subframe. This unique positioning lowers the car's center of gravity, which improves handling and minimizes rollover risk, and replaces the heavy engine block with impact absorbing boron steel rails.\", text=\"Model S is designed from the ground up to be the safest car on the road, as proven by a 5-star rating in all categories of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) crash test. Much of its safety is owed to the unique electric drivetrain that sits beneath the car's aluminum occupant cell in its own subframe. This unique positioning lowers the car's center of gravity, which improves handling and minimizes rollover risk, and replaces the heavy engine block with impact absorbing boron steel rails.\", formatting=None, hyperlink=None), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/20', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=4, bbox=BoundingBox(l=207.3518, t=229.23359999999997, r=587.2518000000003, b=160.26090916030535, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 382))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Side impacts are met by aluminum pillars reinforced with steel rails to reduce intrusion, protecting occupants and the battery pack while improving roof stiffness. In the event of an accident, eight airbags protect front and rear occupants, and the battery system automatically disconnects the main power source. Should the worst happen, there is no safer car to be in than Model S.', text='Side impacts are met by aluminum pillars reinforced with steel rails to reduce intrusion, protecting occupants and the battery pack while improving roof stiffness. In the event of an accident, eight airbags protect front and rear occupants, and the battery system automatically disconnects the main power source. Should the worst happen, there is no safer car to be in than Model S.', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), SectionHeaderItem(self_ref='#/texts/21', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.SECTION_HEADER: 'section_header'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=5, bbox=BoundingBox(l=72.0, t=225.6003, r=179.91120000000006, b=204.96662860040567, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 9))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Autopilot', text='Autopilot', formatting=None, hyperlink=None, level=1), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/22', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=5, bbox=BoundingBox(l=331.2, t=227.48860000000002, r=701.8509999999998, b=128.51590916030534, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 512))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Autopilot combines a forward looking camera, radar, and 360 degree sonar sensors with real time traffic updates to automatically drive Model S on the open road and in dense stop and go traffic. Changing lanes becomes as simple as a tap of the turn signal. When you arrive at your destination, Model S will both detect a parking spot and automatically park itself. Standard equipment safety features are constantly monitoring stop signs, traffic signals and pedestrians, as well as for unintentional lane changes.', text='Autopilot combines a forward looking camera, radar, and 360 degree sonar sensors with real time traffic updates to automatically drive Model S on the open road and in dense stop and go traffic. Changing lanes becomes as simple as a tap of the turn signal. When you arrive at your destination, Model S will both detect a parking spot and automatically park itself. Standard equipment safety features are constantly monitoring stop signs, traffic signals and pedestrians, as well as for unintentional lane changes.', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), SectionHeaderItem(self_ref='#/texts/23', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.SECTION_HEADER: 'section_header'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=7, bbox=BoundingBox(l=54.0, t=518.1603, r=263.95680000000004, b=469.5186286004057, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 32))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Inspired by an endurance athlete', text='Inspired by an endurance athlete', formatting=None, hyperlink=None, level=1), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/24', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=7, bbox=BoundingBox(l=331.2, t=520.0486, r=734.8010000000005, b=421.07590916030534, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 573))], source=[], comments=[], orig=\"Tesla's design and engineering teams have gone to extraordinary lengths to ensure that air flows smoothly above, around and below Model S to reduce drag, which in turn maximizes battery range. The smart air suspension lowers the car's height at highway speeds to reduce its frontal area. Electronically controlled vents stay closed until sensors detect that cooling is necessary. The front bumper routes air uninterrupted beneath the battery's flat skidplate and past the rear diffuser. The result is a seven seat sedan with the stance of a coupe and supercar aerodynamics.\", text=\"Tesla's design and engineering teams have gone to extraordinary lengths to ensure that air flows smoothly above, around and below Model S to reduce drag, which in turn maximizes battery range. The smart air suspension lowers the car's height at highway speeds to reduce its frontal area. Electronically controlled vents stay closed until sensors detect that cooling is necessary. The front bumper routes air uninterrupted beneath the battery's flat skidplate and past the rear diffuser. The result is a seven seat sedan with the stance of a coupe and supercar aerodynamics.\", formatting=None, hyperlink=None), SectionHeaderItem(self_ref='#/texts/25', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.SECTION_HEADER: 'section_header'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=8, bbox=BoundingBox(l=460.8, t=537.6002, r=665.6664000000002, b=488.9585286004057, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 25))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Zero profile door handles', text='Zero profile door handles', formatting=None, hyperlink=None, level=1), TextItem(self_ref='#/texts/26', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.TEXT: 'text'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=8, bbox=BoundingBox(l=460.8, t=463.16859999999997, r=704.9170000000003, b=409.19590916030535, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 212))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Model S door handles are a work of art. When a key is in close proximity, they automatically extend. When no longer in use, they retract into the body of the car, creating a seamless surface for air to pass over.', text='Model S door handles are a work of art. When a key is in close proximity, they automatically extend. When no longer in use, they retract into the body of the car, creating a seamless surface for air to pass over.', formatting=None, hyperlink=None), SectionHeaderItem(self_ref='#/texts/27', parent=RefItem(cref='#/body'), children=[], content_layer=<ContentLayer.BODY: 'body'>, meta=None, label=<DocItemLabel.SECTION_HEADER: 'section_header'>, prov=[ProvenanceItem(page_no=8, bbox=BoundingBox(l=72.0, t=225.6003, r=309.7871999999999, b=204.96662860040567, coord_origin=<CoordOrigin.BOTTOMLEFT: 'BOTTOMLEFT'>), charspan=(0, 21))], source=[], comments=[], orig='Hidden in plain sight', text='Hidden in plain sight', formatting=None, hyperlink=None, level=1), T